        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 24 at 6:38PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 638 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Winchester, or 8 miles
northeast of Oglethorpe, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Saint Louis, Winchester, Marshallville, and Henderson.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
